snippet: Parties in a Texas redistricting dispute agreed to a new set of electoral maps, but the proposal did not have the support of all the groups involved in a related lawsuit.
abstract: State Attorney General Greg Abbott and several minority groups that sued Texas over its redrawing of electoral lines agree to a set of proposed maps that create two new Hispanic-dominated Congressional districts, but other groups involved in the lawsuit do not approve proposal.
lead_paragraph: Parties in a Texas redistricting dispute agreed to a new set of electoral maps, but the proposal did not have the support of all the groups involved in a related lawsuit.

headline.main: Texas: Maps Remain Uncertain as Deadline Passes
